abstract: Waldorf Astoria's Viennese Opera Ball celebrates 60th anniversary of the signing of the Austrian state treaty, agreement that officially ended allied occupation of Austria following World War II; event features 71-year-old Jeep that was used to patrol the occupied territory.
lead_paragraph: A 71-year-old Jeep rolled in, and later out, at the Viennese Opera Ball at the Waldorf Astoria on Friday, a charity gala that was celebrating the 60th anniversary of the signing of the Austrian state treaty.

headline.main: 60 Years Later, a Rolling Tribute on Waldorf Terrain
